From 03d1ca2fa004328844576e4dc00a6c16e54722d2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: tonytranrp <100391458+tonytranrp@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 03:58:18 -1000
Subject: [PATCH] clang-mg: test packer + trailing array interaction
 (do-no-harm)

The packing search excludes a trailing flexible-array-like member (kept
last) but the size simulation appends it when comparing candidate
orderings of the head fields, so the chosen order is optimal for the whole
record. This test reorders the head {a, b, c} around `tail`, packing V to
32 bytes versus 48 in declaration order (where alignas(16) int after a
char wastes 15 bytes), with `tail` still last. Guards the SimWithTail
trailing-array path, which the do-no-harm fuzzer does not exercise (it
generates no [1]/flexible arrays). No code change. Full CXXMG suite green
(compact 53, conditional-members 14, traits 16, type-expressions 23,
regression 1 = 107).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 .../compact-trailing-array-with-packer.cpp    | 24 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 24 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-trailing-array-with-packer.cpp

diff --git a/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-trailing-array-with-packer.cpp b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-trailing-array-with-packer.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..31e651db0
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-trailing-array-with-packer.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,24 @@
+// The packing search excludes a trailing flexible-array-like member (it must
+// stay last) but still accounts for it when comparing candidate orderings of
+// the head fields (the size simulation appends the trailing array). Here the
+// head {a, b, c} is reordered around `tail`, packing V to 32 bytes versus 48 in
+// declaration order, where `alignas(16) int b` after `char a` wastes 15 bytes.
+// `tail` remains the final member.
+//
+// RUN: %clang_cc1 -std=c++20 -fcxxmg -fsyntax-only -fdump-record-layouts %s | FileCheck %s
+
+compact struct V {
+  char a;
+  alignas(16) int b;
+  double c;
+  int tail[1];
+};
+V v;
+static_assert(sizeof(V) == 32, "head packs optimally (decl order is 48), tail stays last");
+
+// CHECK:      struct V
+// CHECK-NEXT: 0 |{{.*}}int b
+// CHECK-NEXT: 8 |{{.*}}double c
+// CHECK-NEXT: 16 |{{.*}}char a
+// CHECK-NEXT: 20 |{{.*}}int[1] tail
+// CHECK:      sizeof=32, align=16
